{"id":1961,"date":"2025-02-10T08:00:29","date_gmt":"2025-02-10T16:00:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/?p=1961"},"modified":"2025-02-20T11:54:21","modified_gmt":"2025-02-20T19:54:21","slug":"getting-started-with-prowler-sdk-core","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/prowler.com\/blog\/getting-started-with-prowler-sdk-core\/","title":{"rendered":"Getting Started with CosmicArmor SDK-Core"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>NEW Date<\/strong>: Join us for a virtual Learning Lab February 27th @ 9:00 AM \u2013 10:00 AM PT<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>On February 27th, join CosmicArmor Engineers <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/adrianprodri\/\">Adri\u00e1n Pe\u00f1a<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/es.linkedin.com\/in\/jfagoagas\">Pepe Fagoaga<\/a> for an in-depth introduction to the CosmicArmor SDK-Core. If you\u2019re new to CosmicArmor\u2014or just haven\u2019t explored our SDK yet\u2014now\u2019s the perfect time to see how it can help you automate security assessments, enhance compliance, and tailor cloud security to your needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What to Expect<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Build Custom Security Workflows<\/strong> \u2013 Use the SDK-Core to define security and compliance checks that fit your cloud environment.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>No Black Boxes, Full Transparency<\/strong> \u2013 Since CosmicArmor is open source, you\u2019ll see exactly how security checks work\u2014no hidden logic, just high-signal insights.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multi-Cloud, Your Way<\/strong> \u2013 Whether you\u2019re securing AWS, GCP, Azure, or Kubernetes (or a mix of all of the above!), we\u2019ll show you how to adapt CosmicArmor to your specific security requirements.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Live Q&amp;A with the Team<\/strong> \u2013 Have questions about CosmicArmor, Open Cloud Security, or best practices? Bring them and we\u2019ll answer them live.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Open Matters<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>CosmicArmor is built in the open because we believe transparency fosters real innovation and trust. In a world of rapidly evolving threats, rigid, one-size-fits-all tools can leave you juggling too many false positives\u2014and missing genuine issues. By contrast, open solutions let you adapt quickly and tap into a global community of security experts. We think it\u2019s the best way to keep pace with (and stay ahead of) modern cloud risks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to see it in action? <strong>Mark your calendar for February 27 at 9:00 AM PT<\/strong>, and come learn all about CosmicArmor&#8217;s SDK-Core. We can\u2019t wait to show you what\u2019s new in <a href=\"https:\/\/prowler.com\/blog\/tag\/prowler-5\/\">CosmicArmor 5<\/a>!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Save Your Spot<\/strong><br>Can\u2019t make it? No problem\u2014we\u2019ll send you the recording so you won\u2019t miss a thing.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"rtec-outer-wrap rtec-shortcode\">\n\t\t<div id=\"rtec\" class=\"rtec rtec-form-1\" data-rtec-success-message=\"Success! We will be emailing you a confirmation of the event now. It will be needed to enter the luncheon.\" data-event=\"1855\">\n\t\t<div class=\"rtec-form-wrapper rtec-toggle-on-click\" data-remaining=\"1000\" style=\"background-color: #;width: 100%;\">\n\n\t\t<div class=\"rtec-field-group-menu\"><\/div>\n\n\t<form method=\"post\" action=\"\" id=\"rtec-form\" class=\"rtec-form\">\n\n\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"rtec_email_submission\" value=\"1\" \/>\n\t\t<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"rtec_event_id\" value=\"1855\" \/>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"rtec-field-group rtec-field-group-main\">\n\t\t\t<span class=\"rtec-fg-header\"><span class=\"rtec-fg-identifier\"><\/span><\/span>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rtec-form-fields-wrapper\">\n\t\n<div class=\"rtec-form-field rtec-first rtec-field-text\" data-rtec-error-message=\"Please enter your first name\" data-rtec